description: Enforce modular boundaries, dependency direction, and placement
alwaysApply: true
---

# Architecture Governance

- Preserve modular architecture and existing folder ownership.
- Place new code in the correct layer (`handler`, `service`, `repository`, `provider`, `infra`) based on responsibility.
- Keep dependency direction explicit: transport -> service -> repository/provider interfaces -> infra implementations.
- Do not place business logic in handlers.
- Do not let module/domain logic import infra concrete implementations directly.
- Avoid cross-module coupling unless explicitly required and documented.
- Validate placement and dependency direction before coding.
